"365",365,"Don Quijote Doflamingo",305,41,3.4e+08,"Captain","living",21,"Don Quixote's crew","inactive",23,1.113e+09,FALSE,"Fruit du Fil","Allows you to take control of someone and use them as a puppet, as well as to easily cut people and objects of various sizes in a large area. It also enables its user to cling to clouds to 'fly', to link several wires together to create a sharp whip, and in a 'combined' version in ball form to 'fire' wire bullets like a pistol shot. And last but not least, he can create a clone from strings that has the same abilities as its owner, and this clone is impervious to bladed weapons. Thanks to his fruit, the user can administer first aid by stitching up organs and open wounds.","Paramecia"
"366",366,"Trébol",349,49,9.9e+07,"Lieutenant-Chef","living",21,"Don Quixote's crew","inactive",23,1.113e+09,FALSE,"Poisse-Poisse fruit","the eater's body can generate mucus at will. This mucus has the following characteristics: sticky, adherent and flammable. It can therefore be used to grip objects, stick to any surface or ignite it.","Paramecia"
"367",367,"Diamante",525,45,9.9e+07,"Lieutenant-Chef","living",21,"Don Quixote's crew","inactive",23,1.113e+09,FALSE,"Fruit of the Wind Thief","Transforms the hard consistency of an object such as a steel cape into that of a flag. Its user can even make a sword 'soft' and then re-solidify it once it has taken on a different shape. It can also become a floating flag in its own right.","Paramecia"
"368",368,"Pica",470,40,9.9e+07,"Lieutenant-Chef","living",21,"Don Quixote's crew","inactive",23,1.113e+09,FALSE,"Fruit de la Caillasse","Allows its holder to melt into stone and create any shape he wishes as an exponentially larger clone of himself. It can alter and control the shape of any rock object or structure at will.","Paramecia"
